f=Product/price/custom/pricing-experiment-discipline/SKILL.md · in=Testing prices packaging real behavior reusing loom's experiment discipline registry, extra rules because revenue experiments touch money, existing customers, trust ways test never does. · p=Stated willingness-to-pay overstates; real revenue experiment tells you what people actually pay. careless price test anger existing customers, distort revenue reporting, breach price commitment pricing experiments run under loom's rigor PLUS blast-radius guardrails. · wu=pricing-research produces WTP hypothesis confirm behavior., packaging-tiers proposes structure validate before launch., price change needs evidence before goes broad (test small first). · st:/ Protocol=INHERIT (loom's experiment-discipline: falsifiable hypothesis, decision rule criteria frozen before data, registry query-first, metric verifies revenue instruments live) BLAST-RADIUS RULES (revenue-specific, additive): (a) NEW customers small holdout default don't silently reprice existing customers test; (b) existing-customer exposure needs explicit sign-off honors price-change-governance (grandfathering); (c) revenue guardrails mandatory conversion win tanks revenue-per-user loss); (d) locked-commitment check test breach price guarantee board scope) RUN (small, reversible, time-boxed) VERDICT (against frozen rule; registered loom's registry) SCALE won test becomes price-change-governance proposal, instant broad change). · in=Inherit loom's rigor fully falsifiable, cheapest, frozen criteria, registry-first, instruments verified; pricing experiments loom experiments, looser cousin. New-customers-or-holdout default existing customers silently repriced test; changing what someone already pays governed change, experiment variable (the trust rule). Revenue guardrails always optimize conversion watch revenue-per-user, churn, expansion; cheaper price lifts signups drops total revenue failed test, win. Locked-commitment check before running price experiment breach guarantee grandfathering promise stops routes board (Governance) locked commitment scope. Won tests scale governance, instantly validated price becomes price-change-governance proposal (impact analysis, grandfathering) before goes broad; experiment earns change, governance ships it. · of=Pricing experiment card: hypothesis variant (new/holdout scope) decision rule revenue guardrails (frozen) locked-commitment check verdict loom registry price-change-governance proposal (if scaling). · pr=loom's rigor PLUS blast-radius rules money experiments carry extra guardrails., Never silently reprice existing customers test., Revenue guardrails mandatory conversion win drops revenue loss., Won tests scale through governance, instantly. · f=Can't run clean pricing test (too new customers)? Use pricing-research competitor evidence, labeled weaker, make first real change small reversible under governance never big untested repricing. · b:with Other Skills=loom owns experiment discipline registry inherits; metric owns revenue instrumentation (verify-live); price adds money-specific guardrails., price-change-governance ships won tests governed changes; board (Governance) gates locked-commitment-touching tests., felix/Finance (future): revenue-per-user margin definitions finance's; price reads them guardrails, co-cited.